Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add
the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and
leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, lay the @British Chicken Thighs{3} flat onto a #baking tray{}.

Sprinkle over the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then rub to coat.

Roast the chicken on the middle shelf until browned and cooked through,
~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.
> It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @Carrot{2}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons
down the length of the carrots, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the carrot, @Rice Vinegar{22%ml}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and
@salt{pinch}. Set aside to pickle.

== Satay Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, add the @Peanut Butter{60%g}, @Sweet Chilli Sauce{64%g},
@Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Hot Water{2%tbsp} for the sauce.

> TIP: If your peanut butter has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for ~{1%min}.

Stir well until smooth. Set your satay sauce aside.

== Coriander Rice and Assembly ==

Roughly chop the @Coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}
in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

When everything's ready, fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and stir through three
quarters of the coriander.

Slice the roasted chicken widthways into 2cm slices.

Share the coriander rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sliced chicken and carrot pickle.

Drizzle the satay sauce over the chicken and finish with a sprinkle of peanuts
and the remaining coriander. Enjoy!